The paper discusses a technique for user identification based on keystroke information captured by a special keyboard or web browser. This falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) as it deals with user identification and authentication. Additionally, the paper focuses on mobile users, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of deep learning techniques for identification suggests that it may also fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the proposed technique, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) or cyber-physical systems (cs.CY).
